sequenceDiagram
    %% Apple Refund Flow
    participant Apple as Apple Server
    participant BackendIOS as iOS Refund View
    participant EventSystem as Payment Refunded Signal

    Apple->>BackendIOS: Send refund notification (POST)
    BackendIOS->>BackendIOS: Parse and verify Apple notification
    alt Notification is "REFUND"
        BackendIOS->>BackendIOS: Check if already processed
        alt Not already processed
            BackendIOS->>BackendIOS: Mark as running
            BackendIOS->>BackendIOS: Extract refund info (ID, time, amount, currency)
            BackendIOS->>EventSystem: Send refund signal
        else Already processing
            BackendIOS->>BackendIOS: Skip refund
        end
    else Not a refund notification
        BackendIOS->>BackendIOS: Ignore and log notification
    end
    BackendIOS-->>Apple: Respond with 200 OK

    %% Google Refund Flow
    participant Admin as Admin User
    participant BackendAndroid as Android Refund View
    participant GoogleAPI as Google API
    participant EventSystem as Payment Refunded Signal

    Admin->>BackendAndroid: Trigger refund check (GET)
    BackendAndroid->>BackendAndroid: Load settings and date range
    BackendAndroid->>GoogleAPI: Request list of refunded purchases
    GoogleAPI-->>BackendAndroid: Return list of voided purchases

    loop For each refunded purchase
        BackendAndroid->>BackendAndroid: Create refund info (ID, time)
        BackendAndroid->>EventSystem: Send refund signal
    end

    BackendAndroid-->>Admin: Return success response
